Christian martyrdom. Images portraying the law and the behavior of tyrannical regimes in terms of the torment of the martyrs signaled the threats to their own legal system. For the first time, the images of martyrs and tyrants are presented as both religious figures and reflections of contemporary thinking about the law.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aChristian martyrs in art. 0aCulture and lawzEuropexHistoryy16th century. 0aCulture and lawzEuropexHistoryy17th century. 0aLaw and artzEuropexHistoryy16th century. 0aLaw and artzEuropexHistoryy17th century. 7aART / History / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2015z9783110438642oZDB-23-DKA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG0 cEPUBz97831103915650 cprintz978311036350040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311036364740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110363647423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110363647.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2015  aZDB-23-DKAb2015